The plot below shows selection signals discovered in the major vector species An. gambiae, An. coluzzii or An. arabiensis, all of which are members of the Anopheles gambiae species complex. The reference genome used for these analyses is the AgamP4 PEST reference. Hover over a signal for more information about the species, location, date and selection statistic in which the signal was found. Click on a signal to see the underlying selection scan data.
